subject: Guet GUI
description:
As PP I want a visual interface so that I can use guet into a project more conveniently without typing commands.


Acceptance Test:
"guet GUI" should launch GUI from command-line

subject: Guet GUI - Add, Set, Get & Remove
description: As a PP I want to add, set, get and remove programmers so that I can manage people in the repository.

subject: Guet GUI - Initialization
description: As a PP I want to initialize guet into the project so that I can use all the guet related functionalities.

subject: Guet GUI - Remove Config
description: As a PP I want to remove guet configuration using interface so that I can remove guet config from the repository I am currently working on.

subject: PP Sessions Tracker
description: As a PP I want to track specific PP sessions so that I can attribute multiple commits to a session.

subject: Get team members from Taiga
description:
As a PP I want to get team members from Taiga so that I can set them as committers.

Acceptance Test:
Successfully display Taiga team members in the guet interface

subject: Build "ads" looking for team members to code with
description: As a PP I want to post ads so that I can inform all the team members that I am looking for one to code with.

subject: Get issues from GitHub project
description: As a PP I want to fetch issues from GitHub so that I can work on them.

subject: Indicate pairing strategy (driver/observer, senior/junior)
description:
As a PP I want to add a pairing strategy so that I can classify programmers in the commit.


Acceptance Test:
I should be able to designate any one committer as primary/driver.

subject: Alphebatize committers list
description: As a PP I want to fetch committers list in alphabetical order so that I can find committers easily.

subject: Warn a user when set committers and commit committers differ
description: As a PP I want to warn the user when set committers and commit committers are different so that I can avoid errors.

subject: guet command not found (Windows)
description:
As a PP I want to be able to use guet on windows machines so that I do not have to use any workarounds.


Acceptance Test:
guet init
guet add
guet set 
guet get
guet remove
guet yeet


Following commands should work in windows command-line.
